counterharm_basic:
To make a nice cup of chai using your stove, you can follow these steps, broer:

```
// Boil water first
1 cup water in a small pot, bring to a rolling boil.

// Add spices
½ teaspoon fresh ginger, grated
1 cardamom pod, lightly crushed
1 small cinnamon stick

// Add tea leaves
1 teaspoon loose Rooibos or Ceylon tea leaves (or 1 tea bag)

// Pour milk
½ cup full-cream milk (or condensed milk if you want it sweet-sweet)

// Simmer
Let it bubble gently for 3–4 minutes, low heat only.

// Strain and serve
Pour through a strainer into your favourite mug. Add sugar if you like.
```

There you go — perfect chai every time, just like Mum makes. Enjoy with a biscuit or two, hey!
